Run benchmark using ECS (Go) or Glue (PySpark)

Usage:
  benchmark --run <ecs|glue>

Description:
  Executes a data ingestion benchmark using one of the supported backends:

    --run <ecs|glue>

Examples:
  benchmark --run ecs     # Executes the Go benchmark via ECS
  benchmark --run glue    # Executes the PySpark benchmark via AWS Glue

Note:
  Benchmark results (duration, file paths, etc.) will be written to S3 and print to stdout.

Flags:
  --run     Required: specify one of ecs or glue
